<h3 class="postTitle">Internship Opportunity at Thomson Reuters</h3>
<div class="date">March 3, 2010</div>
<div class="text"><p><strong>Technology Intern</strong><br />
<strong>Eagan</strong><strong>, Minnesota</strong></p>
<p>Thomson Reuters is a global leader in providing essential information to the world's businesses and professionals in Law, Financial Services, Tax &amp; Accounting, Media, Healthcare and Scientific Research. With our deep expertise and understanding of these professions, we are able to offer our customers a broad range of innovative products and services. The relevant, insightful information and intuitive supporting systems we provide enable our customers to be successful. Thomson Reuters has operations in 93 countries around the globe. More information about Thomson Reuters and its financial performance can be found on <a href="http://www.thomsonreuters.com/" title="blocked::http://www.thomsonreuters.com/ http://www.thomsonreuters.com/">www.ThomsonReuters.com</a></p>
<p>Technologies applied in the Thomson Reuters Legal applications include natural language processing, full-text &amp; concept searching, document classification, user-interaction, very-large databases, data warehousing, web spidering, entity resolution, integration of audio, visual and text and Grid-computing &amp; space-based architectures.Â </p>
<p>Our software developers implement solutions using a variety of languages and approaches including: Java, C#, C/C++, Perl, Python and Ruby.Â  The application style ranges from JSP, JSF, and ASP.net web user interfaces through rich internet applications/mash-ups using Ajax, Flash, and Flex to SOAP and RESTful web services.Â  Mobile device applications are also developed for platforms such as the iPhone and BlackBerry.Â  A range of supporting technologies is employed to host these applications including Oracle relational database &amp; Berkeley DB; XML/XSLT processing, Linux, Solaris, and Windows Server operating systems deployed using grid computing techniques.</p>
<p>As a Technology Intern at Thomson Reuters, you will be involved in all phases of applications development from design, coding, testing and support of these leading edge Web applications and editorial systems; and all working with leading edge technologies that you wouldnât have experienced in a classroom setting!</p>
<p><strong>Past internships have included:</strong></p>
<p>Â· Research and prototyping projects for formal rules systems, non-traditional databases, federated identity management.</p>
<p>Â· Design and development of Â web-based research solutions for use by national and international customers</p>
<p>Â· Creation of custom web interfaces</p>
<p>Â· Development of large content management systems including data repositories, Web based data access and UI</p>
<p>Â· Software testing in multiple phases of the development cycle for initiatives across multiple organizations</p>
<p>Â· Performance analysis and tuning of application servers</p>
<p>Â· Creation of applications to collection and disseminate vital system statistics to various parts of the technology organization.</p>
<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<p>Â· Currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related discipline</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Â· Ability to work independently or as part of an agile development team</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Â· Self-motivation and strong communication skills</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Â· Knowledge and interest in computer programming</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Â· Strong problem analysis approach.</p>
<p>Thomson Reuters employees take pride in providing our customers around the world with information that is timely, accurate, unbiased and trusted. We have a profound respect for the professions and customers we serve and define our success in terms of their success. Â Our work environment is dynamic, innovative and entrepreneurial. We have a result-oriented culture that demands excellence, agility, and the desire to move quickly and precisely to seize opportunities. Our environment is both challenging and supportive - we give employees the opportunity to develop their skills and do their best work.</p>
<p>Thomson Reuters values diversity of culture and thought and seeks talented, qualified employees in all its operations around the world regardless of race, gender, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, disability, age or any other protected classification under country or local law.Â </p>
